    {
      "text": "<p>You should add an <code>h4</code> element for each of your <code>&#x3C;div class=\"col-xs-6\"></code> elements.</p>",
      "testString": "const columnSixes = document.querySelectorAll('.col-xs-6');\r\nconst columnSixOneChildren = columnSixes?.[0]?.querySelectorAll(`:scope ${'h4'}`);\r\nassert.lengthOf(columnSixOneChildren,1); \r\n\r\nconst columnSixTwoChildren = columnSixes?.[1]?.querySelectorAll(`:scope ${'h4'}`);\r\nassert.lengthOf(columnSixTwoChildren,1); "
    },
    {
      "text": "<p>One <code>h4</code> element should have the text <code>#left-well</code>.</p>",
      "testString": "const firstH4 = document.querySelectorAll('h4')?.[0]; \r\nassert.match(firstH4?.textContent,/#left-well/gi); "
    },
    {
      "text": "<p>One <code>h4</code> element should have the text <code>#right-well</code>.</p>",
      "testString": "const secondH4 = document.querySelectorAll('h4')?.[1]; \r\nassert.match(secondH4?.textContent,/#right-well/gi); "
    },
    {
      "text": "<p>All <code>h4</code> elements should have closing labels.</p>",
      "testString": "assert.match(code,/<\\/h4>/g);\r\nassert.match(code,/<h4/g);\r\nassert.equal(code.match(/<\\/h4>/g).length , code.match(/<h4/g).length);"
    }
  ],
  "description": "<section id=\"description\">\n<p>For clarity, let's make all our well labels have their own numbers.</p>\n<p>Above your left well, inside its <code>col-xs-6</code> <code>div</code> element, add an <code>h4</code> element with the text <code>#left-well</code>.</p>\n<p>Above your right well, inside its <code>col-xs-6</code> <code>div</code> element, add an <code>h4</code> element with the text <code>#right-well</code>.</p>\n</section>",
